canonical:
  title: 東郊馬上
  author: 郭預
  language: lzh
  text: 信馬尋春事牛兒方力耕鳥鳴天氣暖魚泳浪紋平野蝶成團戲沙鷗作隊行自嫌隨燕雀不似鷺鷥淸
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 東郊馬上
  author: 郭預
  language: lzh
  text: 信馬尋春事。牛兒方力耕。鳥鳴天氣暖。魚泳浪紋平。野蝶成團戲。沙鷗作隊行。自嫌隨燕雀。不似鷺鷥淸。
korean:
  title: 동교 마상
  author: 곽예
  language: kor
  text: |-
    말 가는 대로 봄 소식을 찾아보니
    소들이 한창 밭을 갈고 있네
    날씨가 따스하니 새들이 짹짹
    물결도 잔잔한데 고기들 굼실굼실
    들나비는 서로 뭉쳐서 희롱하고
    모래 갈매기는 떼를 지어 다니누나
    시시한 연작들과 추축하는 나
    저기 저 해오라기처럼 청한하지 못하구나
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0120_010_0710&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: On Horseback at the Eastern Suburb
  author: Gwak Ye
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Following where my horse takes me, I seek the signs of spring—
    Oxen labor in the fields, their strength at full stride.
    Warm weather draws the birds to sing their calls,
    While fish glide through the smooth and rippling waters.
    Wild butterflies gather in playful swarms,
    And sandpipers in flocks trace paths across the shore.
    Yet here I am, keeping company with sparrows and swallows,
    Falling short of the noble crane's serene and spotless grace.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: The heron (해오라기, heaoragi) symbolizes purity, nobility, and transcendence in East Asian poetry, contrasting with the speaker's more earthly observations.
  - key: ''
    value: The poem captures a moment of spring wandering while subtly reflecting on the poet's own position and limitations within the natural and social order.
